t Society—civil rights, the economy, social legislation, housing, and the Vietnam War—Busby not only articulated and refined Johnson's political thinking, he also helped shape the most ambitious, far-reaching legislative agenda since FDR's New Deal. Here is Johnson the politician, Johnson the schemer, Johnson who advised against JFK’s choice of an open limousine that fateful day in Dallas, and Johnson the father, sickened by the deaths of young men fighting and dying in Vietnam on his orders. The Thirty-first of March is a rare glimpse into the inner sanctum of Johnson's presidency, as seen through the eyes of one of the people who understood him best.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  apresidential history, presidential advisor, Kennedy assassination, Great Society, Great Society program, LBJ, Vietnam, political history, us presidents, American history, Texas politicians.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079782440uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32747040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477327487423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477327487/original  a978-3-11-079782-4  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles